                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <p class="leading">
                            Most websites wait. Visitors arrive, look around, and leave —
                            without ever making contact. Not because they weren't interested.
                            Because nobody was there to respond.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="grid-12 padding-y-xl">
                        <article class="card md-col-6 contrast-card--wrong">
                            <p>You never knew they were there. You never got the chance to respond. The opportunity passed, and
                                another business got the sale — not because they had a better product, but because someone was there
                                to answer when a visitor showed up.</p>
                            <p>It's the gap between a visitor arriving and a conversation starting. That gap is where your revenue
                                disappears.</p>
                        </article>
                        <article class="card md-col-6 contrast-card--wrong">
                            <p>The problem isn't your product. It's not your traffic. It's not your pricing.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Contact forms get ignored. People don't want to fill in forms and wait two days for a reply.</li>
                                <li>No one's available 24/7. Visitors arrive at 11pm, on weekends, when your team is offline.</li>
                                <li>You don't know what they wanted. A visitor who leaves silently takes their budget with them.</li>
                                <li>Your competitors respond faster. The first business to engage a serious buyer usually wins.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row padding-y-xl">
                        <blockquote class="leading">
                            The average business website converts less than 3% of its visitors into leads. That means for every 100
                            people who find you, 97 leave without you ever knowing they existed.
                        </blockquote>
                    </div>
